"The 3D cursor is the most intuitive of the pivot points. With the 3D "
"cursor selected as the active pivot point (from either the *Editors "
"Header* or via :kbd:`.`), simply position the 3D cursor and then do the "
"required transformation. All rotation and scaling transformations will "
"now be done relative to the location of the 3D cursor."
